<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Beef" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Beef,</orth> 1) the animal Bos taurus; only in the plural: <cit><quote>flesh of muttons, beefes or goats,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.168" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 168</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>now has he land and beeves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.353" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 353</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) the flesh of oxen prepared for food: <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 8.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 23</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 23</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 23</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.3.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 3, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.7.161" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 7, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.10.61" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 10, 61</bibl>. cf. <cit><quote>bull-beeves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 9</bibl></cit>. An obscene meaning seems hidden in <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 59</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 28</bibl>. Prince Henry calls Falstaff his <cit><quote>sweet b.,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.199" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 3, 199</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>